senselogic.sitevision.api.property

Interface Properties<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - native script value

    @Requireable(value="Properties")
public interface Properties<T>
    Utility interface for getting multiple Node property values in server-side Javascript.

    Extraction of property values from Nodes are typically performed using PropertyUtil but this utility is less obtrusive to work with in server-side script contexts (WebApps, RESTApps, Script module etc.).

    Property value types
    The value of a JCR Node property can be resolved as different types. For instance a property with primary type PropertyType.DATE can be resolved as Calendar or as String. This utility returns values with a specific type:

    • The numerical timestamp will be returned as value for properties of type PropertyType.DATE.
    • The Node identifier will be returned as value for properties of type PropertyType.WEAKREFERENCE.

    Example
    Below is an example that demonstrates the behaviour and usage of this utility. 

       var properties = require('Properties');
   ...

   // get examples

   // Returns the identifier of the given Node, e.g: '4.540818ed12a6539aa3f80001645'
   pageId = properties.get(pageNode);

   // Returns the URI property value of the given Node, e.g. '/4.540818ed12a6539aa3f80001645.html'
   pageUri = properties.get(pageNode, 'URI');

   // Returns the displayName property value of the given Node, e.g. 'The page'
   pageName = properties.get(pageNode, 'displayName');
   pageName = properties.get(pageId, 'displayName');
   pageName = properties.get(pageUri, 'displayName');

   // Returns a native script object with given properties (that exist) of the specified Node e.g:
   // {
   //    URI: '/4.540818ed12a6539aa3f80001645.html',
   //    displayName: 'The page',
   //    published: true,
   //    publishDate: 1227618333142
   // }
   pageData = properties.get(pageNode, 'URI', 'displayName', 'published', 'publishDate', 'nameOfNonExistingProperty');

   // getArray examples

   // Returns the identifier of the given Node as array, e.g: ['4.540818ed12a6539aa3f80001645']
   pageIdArray = properties.getArray(pageNode);

   // Returns the identifier for the children of given Node as array, e.g:
   // [
   //    '19.540818ed12a6539aa3f80006889',
   //    '4.540818ed12a6539aa3f80001645_pageContent',
   //    ...
   // ]
   childIdsArray = properties.getArray(pageNode.getNodes());

   // Returns the displayName for the nodes of a menu from a given Node as array, e.g:
   // [
   //    'The Page',
   //    'Another Page',
   //    ...
   // ]
   menuNamesArray = properties.getArray(nodeIteratorUtil.getMenuItems(pageNode), 'displayName');

   // Returns the displayName and URI for the hits of a SearchResult as array, e.g:
   // [
   //    {
   //       displayName: 'Public API'
   //       URI: '/docs/public-api',
   //    },
   //    {
   //       displayName: 'REST API'
   //       URI: '/docs/rest-api',
   //    },
   //    ...
   // ]
   hitsDataArray = properties.getArray(searchResult, 'displayName', 'URI');

    Security reminder! All output should always be escaped to prevent XSS!

    • When implementing a WebApp, you would typically use get(Object, String...) or getArray(Object, String...) and output the value with underscore escape (e.g. <%- theValueToEscape %>).
    • In other server-side scripting contexts (e.g. the Script module) you would typically use getEscaped(Object, String...) or getArrayEscaped(Object, String...) and output the (already) escaped value using Velocity (e.g. $theEscapedValue).
    Since:
    Sitevision 4.5.2

      • get

        T get(Object aJcrNodeResolvable,
      String... aPropertyNames)
throws Exception
        Gets named properties from a given Node-resolvable object.

        See code examples in the interface description above.

        Parameters:
        aJcrNodeResolvable - something that can be resolved as a Node. Typically a Node, a Node identifier or a relative URL of a Node (the URI property)
        aPropertyNames - the names of the properties of interest
        Returns:
        the properties as a native Javascript object
        Throws:
        Exception - if the scripting engine fails to convert property values to a native Javascript object
        See Also:
        getEscaped(Object, String...)

      • getEscaped

        T getEscaped(Object aJcrNodeResolvable,
             String... aPropertyNames)
      throws Exception
        Gets escaped named properties from a given Node-resolvable object.

        This method is equivalent with get(Object, String...) except that all string values will be escaped.

        Parameters:
        aJcrNodeResolvable - something that can be resolved as a Node. Typically a Node, a Node identifier or a relative URL of a Node (the URI property)
        aPropertyNames - the names of the properties of interest
        Returns:
        the escaped properties as a native Javascript object
        Throws:
        Exception - if the scripting engine fails to convert property values to a native Javascript object
        Since:
        Sitevision 6.2

      • getArray

        T getArray(Object aIterable,
           String... aPropertyNames)
    throws Exception
        Processes an iterable object and returns an array of named properties for each Node-resolvable object that is iterated.

        This method is conceptually equivalent with the get method but the core functionality of this method is to process something that can be iterated in order to handle multiple nodes and deliver properties for them as an array.

        See code examples in the interface description above.

        Parameters:
        aIterable - something that can be resolved as a Node or something that can be iterated and contains objects that can be resolved as a Node. Typically an array, NodeIterator, SearchResult, Collection or FilterSplit (the accepted nodes will be processed)
        aPropertyNames - the names of the properties of interest
        Returns:
        a native Javascript array with properties
        Throws:
        Exception - if the scripting engine fails to convert property values to a native Javascript object
        Since:
        Sitevision 6.1
        See Also:
        NodeIteratorUtil, getArrayEscaped(Object, String...)

      • getArrayEscaped

        T getArrayEscaped(Object aIterable,
                  String... aPropertyNames)
           throws Exception
        Processes an iterable object and returns an array of escaped named properties for each Node-resolvable object that is iterated.

        This method is equivalent with getArray(Object, String...) except that all string values will be escaped.

        Parameters:
        aIterable - something that can be resolved as a Node or something that can be iterated and contains objects that can be resolved as a Node. Typically an array, NodeIterator, SearchResult, Collection or FilterSplit (the accepted nodes will be processed)
        aPropertyNames - the names of the properties of interest
        Returns:
        a native Javascript array with escaped properties
        Throws:
        Exception - if the scripting engine fails to convert property values to a native Javascript object
        Since:
        Sitevision 6.2
